  "A farmer in the Midwest notices declining yields despite increasing fertilizer application. Soil tests reveal low organic matter, compacted soil structure, and reduced microbial activity. A county extension agent recommends switching to cover crops, no-till practices, and crop rotation. How would these three practices work together to restore soil health?": "",
