  "Only crop rotation would help; the other two practices are unnecessary": "",
  "These practices would further reduce yields because they eliminate modern farming techniques": "",
  "These practices form an integrated soil health system: cover crops add organic matter and protect soil, no-till preserves soil structure and supports beneficial organisms, and crop rotation (especially with legumes) breaks pest cycles and naturally adds nitrogen.": "",
  "A large-scale cattle operation in South America is located on recently cleared rainforest land. The ranch produces beef exported to developed countries. An environmental assessment reveals the operation contributes to deforestation, methane emissions, water pollution from manure, and biodiversity loss. Which sustainability dimensions are being violated?": "",
