  "All three solutions are equally effective and interchangeable": "",
  "These solutions are too small-scale to have any meaningful impact": "",
  "The food waste hierarchy prioritizes prevention (right-sizing portions) over reduction (local sourcing to minimize spoilage) over recycling (composting). Preventing waste is always more efficient than managing waste after it occurs.": "",
  "A region is experiencing a pest outbreak that threatens crop yields. A conventional farmer applies broad-spectrum pesticides immediately. A neighboring farm using IPM monitors pest populations, introduces natural predators, applies targeted biological controls, and only uses a narrow-spectrum pesticide on the most affected areas. What are the sustainability advantages of the IPM approach?": "",
