  "No improvements because precision agriculture uses the same total amount of fertilizer": "",
  "The dead zone would immediately disappear once precision agriculture was adopted": "",
  "Precision agriculture uses GPS, sensors, and data analysis to apply fertilizer only where needed, reducing total application and minimizing excess that runs off into waterways. This would lower nitrate contamination in tap water and reduce nutrient loading contributing to the dead zone.": "",
